Sentencas: In this study, three low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells are constructed using Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) as the electrolyte and Ni-LiNi0.8Co0.15Al0.05O2 (Ni-NCAL) and Ni-Ag as the electrodes.
Titulo: Effects of LiNi0.8Co0.15Al0.05O2 electrodes on the conduction mechanism of Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-d electrolyte and performance of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
